  "text": "Extending from quadrilateral bounding box, it's natural to use bounding 'boxes' with more that 4 vertexes. Bounding polygons [CITATION_1] with as many as 14 vertexes are proposed, followed by a bi-lstm [CITATION_2] layer to refine the coordinates of the predicted vertexes. In their framework, however, axis-aligned rectangles are extracted as intermediate results in the first step, and the location bounding polygons are predicted upon them.",
